      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COME ON GLAMOUR (4) returns from a three-month spell. Came of age last prep winning three of her last four runs, all at today's journey. Has a fine fresh record and handles all going so she has every base covered. Rising ten-year-old BRAZEN BRANDO (7) continued his fine form of late when runner-up in a similar race to this at Port Macquarie last start. Relishes the heavy tracks and is a 1000m specialist. Sure to give a great sight again from the favourable draw. THE PICCOLINO (8) hasn't won for 12 months but did finish third here at this trip two back, the best of five runs this prep. Handles the heavy ground so this looks a nice race for him. SILENT SERENADE (6) last appeared when successful over 1400m at Tamworth on 23 February. Placed at both first-up runs and in the money at all four 1000m outings. Must be respected. CASHAWAY GOLD (2) resumes. Led all the way to win here at this trip on a soft track when fresh from a spell last prep. Has the right profile.",
